Chinese Blogger Jailed for a Year After Writing About Party Chief, FT Says

-- B y   B i l l y   C h a n
-- 
2011-06-08T00:33:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/chinese-blogger-jailed-for-a-year-after-writing-about-party-chief-ft-says.html
A 45-year-old Chinese man was sent to
a labor camp after posting a blog attacking Bo Xilai, the
Communist party chief of Chongqing city, the Financial Times
reported, citing the son of the imprisoned man.  Fang Hong was detained by the police on April 24 for
“fabricating facts and disturbing public order” and was
sentenced to one year in the labor camp, the report said. Fang
posted a blog criticial of Bo’s alleged role in the trial of
lawyer Li Zhuang, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Billy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
 bchan101@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
